 (1976).  He received his <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../722/236722.xml">
M.Sc.</link> in mathematics from <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../601/1617601.xml">
Courant Institute</link>  (1979) and <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../775/8775.xml">
Ph.D.</link> from <university wordnetid="108286163" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../455/7954455.xml">
New York University</link></university>
 in 1981; his advisor was <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../038/9638038.xml">
S. R. S. Varadhan</link>, and his dissertation was entitled <it>Invariant Measures of Diffusion Processes on Domains with Boundaries</it>.<ref xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="#xpointer(//reflist/entry[@id=%221%22])">1</ref>  He worked at <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../712/3712.xml">
Bell Labs</link> (1981-2007), before joining <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../696/562696.xml">
MathWorks</link> of <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../853/116853.xml">
Natick</link>.  Weiss had longer appointments with <university wordnetid="108286163" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../315/239315.xml">
University of Maryland, College Park</link></university>
 (1986), <university wordnetid="108286163" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<ranking wordnetid="114429484" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../310/6310.xml">
Columbia University</link></ranking>
</university>
 (1993) and <university wordnetid="108286163" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../135/295135.xml">
Drew University</link></university>
 (2005).
